(*TODAY ONLY*)

Double cardboard combo with heavy packing on all sides 🍟

Large items like artwork can be bulky, heavy, & kind of daunting to package! 

My overall tip is use CARDBOARD. It works great for padding your pieces, can be repurposed into other boxes, and it’s relatively easy to find - for FREE🙌🏻📦

Find a good packaging material & go heavy with it- I have a supply of large leftover paper sheets, which make fantastic padding. 

Use what you can find, and source the rest! 

Prioritize the items that save you time & make your life easier! (E.g. Standard size boxes, package scale, shipping labels, etc..) 🤗

What are your best packaging tips?
